cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper deals with graph visualization, which is a subfield of computer graphics and visualization. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to estimate aesthetic metrics, which falls under the subfield of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses graph kernels, which are commonly used in machine learning for graph-based data, and thus, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions using image processing techniques to visualize graphs, which falls under the subfield of computer vision, cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses a user study, which involves human perception and thus, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible sub-category.
